I often go to this restaurant, as it’s right across the street from the train station.  Each and every time I go I order fish NO ONION. I mean the cashier asks if I want onion, and each and every time I say no onion.  But for some reason if I’m not looking as they share the fish I always end up with onion.  That I’m allergic to.  When I get home, I end up not being able to eat it, something I spent my money on.  The last time this happen, I told the lady behind the counter I said no onion, I want a different serving.  Attitude, “well once we hand it to you over the counter we can’t take it back.  “What??! I paid you all made an error” today I go there, they have big note on the wall. Tell the cashier what you want and watch what as your food is being shared, because there will be no refund and no exchange.  Excuse me? How about I report you to the business bureau and let’s not forget about the GRADE PENDING from the health inspection. If I had zero stars to give that’s what FISHERMAN COVE ON ROCKAWAY PARKWAY  would have gotten.
